{{Top|notoc=1}}
{{Quote|It is protected by an energy shield which is generated from the nearby forest moon of Endor. The shield must be deactivated if any attack is to be attempted.|[[Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar]], regarding the assault on the second Death Star|<ref name="RoTJ">{{Film|VI}}</ref>}}
[[File:Endor_trooper_shield.png|thumb|right|250px|Rebel troopers activate a shield generator to protect themselves from [[All Terrain Scout Transport|AT-ST]] fire.]]
A '''deflector shield generator''', also called a '''shield generator''',<ref name="RoTJ" /> a '''shield projector''',<ref name="Build XWing 1">{{BuildXWingCite|1|Rocket Science}}</ref> or a '''shield array''',<ref name="Quest for Planet X">''[[The High Republic: Quest for Planet X]]''</ref> was a device which was used to create a protective [[deflector shield]],<ref name="SW EOSAOV (SE)">''[[Star Wars Encyclopedia of Starfighters and Other Vehicles (second edition)]]''</ref> such as a [[ray shield]].<ref name="RoTJ" />

The [[Galactic Empire]] based a [[SLD-26 planetary shield generator]] on the forest [[moon]] of [[Endor]].<ref name="Ultimate">''[[Ultimate Star Wars]]''</ref> The shield provided protection for the Empire's powerful [[DS-2 Death Star II Mobile Battle Station]] [[superweapon]] and, so long as it was active, made the weapon invulnerable to the [[Battle of Endor|attacks]] of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance]] forces.<ref name="RoTJ" />

During the time of the [[Clone Wars]], the militaries of the [[Unknown Regions]] used [[electrostatic barrier]]s similar in purpose to the deflector shield generators used in the majority of [[the galaxy]], but much less powerful.<ref name="Chaos Rising">''[[Thrawn Ascendancy: Chaos Rising]]''</ref> This led Thrawn to bring a deflector shield generator he termed a "Republic energy shield" from the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems|Separatist]] [[Mokivj droid factory|droid factory]] on [[Mokivj]] back to his [[Chiss|people]] after assisting [[Jedi Knight]] [[Anakin Skywalker]] on his [[mission to Batuu]].<ref name="Thrawn: Alliances">''[[Thrawn: Alliances]]''</ref> Thrawn would later use the "Republic energy shield" in the [[Battle over Primea]] to help defeat the [[Nikardun]] [[general]] [[Yiv]] the Benevolent, thus ending the [[Nikardun conquests]].<ref name="Chaos Rising" />

